com.mousebird.maply

Class ShapeLinear

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mousebird.maply.Shape
      • com.mousebird.maply.ShapeLinear

  • public class ShapeLinear
extends Shape
    A linear feature offset from the globe.
    The main difference between this object and a regular MaplyVectorObject is that you specify coordiantes in 3D. You can use this to create linear features that are offset from the globe.

      • setCoords

        public void setCoords(Point3d[] coords)
        The coordinates used to draw the lines.
        The x and y values are in geographic. The z values are offsets from the globe (or map) and are in display units. For the globe display units are based on a radius of 1.0.
